      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u, but u seem pretty certain that the \"trickle-down\" view is just a fallacy. if i'm writing this paper for a grad seminar, i need to understand if there's any legitimate empirical data supporting the idea that capital flight or reduced investment is a real risk, or if that's just a political talking point. is there any actual consensus on this in economists' circles, or is it all just one-sided?",
